  ('en', 'Expressions connues', 'At the beginning of the twentieth century, in what place was it common to « make a cigarette » ?', 'Theater', 'Circus', 'Hospital', 'Court', '1', 'At the beginning of the 20th century, for a theater actor, the expression « to have the big tobacco » meant in fact « to be very applauded ».', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theatre'),
  ('en', 'Expressions connues', 'How do you go if you do it « without fanfare » ?', 'Without noise', 'Without clothes', 'Without money', 'Without family', '1', 'Coming from the military world in 1650, this expression is generalized to all actions carried out discreetly or secretly.', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Silence'),
